BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 410.50 Tm (This is the map of the whole framework, so let's read it top to bottom. At the very top is the Iterable) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 395.50 Tm (interface - anything iterable can be used in a for-each loop. Below it is Collection, the root of most) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 380.50 Tm (of what we use. Collection branches into three: List, which is ordered, index-based, and allows) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 365.50 Tm (duplicates; Set, which forbids duplicates; and Queue, which deals with items at the ends. Each of) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 350.50 Tm (those has concrete classes - ArrayList and LinkedList for List, HashSet and TreeSet for Set, and) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 335.50 Tm (so on. Now notice the box on its own at the bottom: Map. This is the one thing to lock in from this) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 320.50 Tm (slide.) Tj ET
