BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 738.00 Tm (Every collection uses generics, so let's give them one slide. Look at the left panel - the old style.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 723.00 Tm (We make an ArrayList with no type. We add the String 'Ravi', and then we accidentally add the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 708.00 Tm (number 101. The compiler says nothing. Later we pull element one out as a String and the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 693.00 Tm (program crashes at runtime with a ClassCastException. The bug hid until production. Now the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 678.00 Tm (right panel - the same code, but we declare ArrayList of String. The moment we try to add 101, the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 663.00 Tm (compiler stops us. The mistake is caught immediately, while we are still typing. That gives us three) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 648.00 Tm (wins, shown in the cards: compile-time type checking; no casting needed, because the compiler) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 633.00 Tm (already knows the type; and self-documenting code, because the angle-bracket String states our) Tj ET
