BT /F1 10.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 603.90 Tm (Department referencing Employees \(weak ownership\).) Tj ET
0.720 0.720 0.760 rg 58.00 590.40 3.00 49.00 re f
BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.040 0.340 0.780 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 580.40 Tm (SAY \(read aloud\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 564.40 Tm (Both of these are HAS-A relationships - one object holds another - but the difference is ownership) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 549.40 Tm (strength, and it is the thing freshers most often confuse. On the left is composition - strong) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 534.40 Tm (ownership. The House creates its own Room inside its constructor. The Room belongs entirely to) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 519.40 Tm (the House; if the House is destroyed, the Room goes with it. A Room without a House makes no) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 504.40 Tm (sense. That is composition. On the right is aggregation - weak ownership. The Department holds a) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 489.40 Tm (list of Employees, but the Employees existed before being added and continue to exist if the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 474.40 Tm (Department is disbanded. An Employee can move to another department. The Department) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 459.40 Tm (references them but does not own their lifecycle.) Tj ET
